Task: Make unread sidebar titles explicitly bold

Summary:
- Added an explicit Pango font-weight helper for sidebar conversation titles.
- Applied bold title weight when unread_count > 0 and normal title weight otherwise.
- Applied the same unread title weight behavior to Ctrl-K conversation switcher rows.
- Updated sidebar design docs and added regression coverage for the weight decision.

Modified files:
- src/window.rs
- docs/sidebar-design.md
- conductor/tracks.md
- conductor/tracks/unread_sidebar_bold_20260707/spec.md
- conductor/tracks/unread_sidebar_bold_20260707/plan.md
- conductor/tracks/unread_sidebar_bold_20260707/metadata.json

Rationale:
The previous implementation relied on the libadwaita heading style class, which did not reliably make unread row titles bold in the navigation list. Explicit Pango title weights make the read/unread visual distinction deterministic.
